rong></li><li><a href=\"#\"><strong>Eigenschaften</strong></a><ol><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/constructor\"><code>Object.prototype.constructor</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/proto\"><code>Object.prototype.__proto__</code></a></li></ol></li><li><a href=\"#\"><strong>Methoden</strong></a><ol><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__defineGetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__defineGetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__defineSetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__defineSetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__lookupGetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__lookupGetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__lookupSetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__lookupSetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/hasOwnProperty\"><code>Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty()</code></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/isPrototypeOf\"><code>Object.prototype.isPrototypeOf()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/propertyIsEnumerable\"><code>Object.prototype.propertyIsEnumerable()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/setPrototypeOf\"><code>Object.setPrototypeOf()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toLocaleString\"><code>Object.prototype.toLocaleString()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toString\"><code>Object.prototype.toString()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/valueOf\"><code>Object.prototype.valueOf()</code></a></li></ol></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div id=\"sect1\"></div>\n\n<p>Die&nbsp;<strong><code>length</code></strong>&nbsp;Eigenschaft&nbsp;repräsentiert&nbsp;die&nbsp;Länge&nbsp;eines&nbsp;Strings.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<pre class=\"syntaxbox notranslate\"><code><var>str</var>.length</code></pre>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"description","title":"Beschreibung","isH3":false,"content":"<p>Die&nbsp;<strong><code>length</code></strong>&nbsp;Eigenschaft gibt die Anzahl der Codeteile des Strings zurück. Javascript verwendet&nbsp;<a title=\"UTF-16\" href=\"https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/UTF-16\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">UTF-16</a>. , also einen 16-Bit Code zur Kodierung der meisten Zeichen, aber zur Darstellung weniger verbreiteter Zeichen werden 2 Codes benötigt. Es ist also durchaus möglich, dass der zurückgegebene Wert nicht der Anzahl der Zeichen in einem String entspricht.</p>\n\n<p>ECMAScript 2016 (ed. 7) Spezifikation&nbsp;definiert&nbsp;eine maximale Länge von <code>2<sup>53</sup> - 1 </code>Elementen.<br>\n Vor dieser Spezifikation&nbsp;war keine maximale Länge an Elementen definiert.</p>\n\n<p class=\"syntaxbox\">Ein leerer String hat die Länge 0.</p>\n\n<p>Die statische String-Eigenschaft gibt den Wert 1 zurück.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Beispiele","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"example_basic_usage","title":"Grundlegende&nbsp;Nutzung","isH3":true,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> str <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">'Mozilla'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> leerstr <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">''</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'Mozilla ist '</span> <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> str<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>length <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> <span class=\"token string\">' Zeichen lang'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">/* \"Mozilla ist 7 Zeichen lang\" */</span>\n\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'Der leere String hat eine Länge von '</span> <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> leerstr<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>length <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> <span class=\"token string\">'Zeichen'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">/* \"Der leere String hat eine Länge von 0 Zeichen\" */</span>\n</code></pre></div>","titleAsText":"Grundlegende Nutzung"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"spezifikationen","title":"Spezifikationen","isH3":false,"content":"<table class=\"standard-table\">\n <tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Spezifikation</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Status</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Kommentar</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://www.ecma-international.org/publications/files/ECMA-ST-ARCH/ECMA-262,%201st%20edition,%20June%201997.pdf\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" title=\"Die 'ECMAScript 1st Edition (ECMA-262)' Spezifikation\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript 1st Edition (ECMA-262)</a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-standard\">Standard</span></td>\n   <td>Initiale Deinition. Implementiert in JavaScript 1.0.</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://www.ecma-international.org/ecma-262/5.1/#sec-15.5.5.1\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript 5.1 (ECMA-262)<br><small lang=\"de\">Die Definition von 'String.prototype.length' in dieser Spezifikation.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-standard\">Standard</span></td>\n   <td>&nbsp;</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://www.ecma-international.org/ecma-262/6.0/#sec-properties-of-string-instances-length\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript 2015 (6th Edition, ECMA-262)<br><small lang=\"de\">Die Definition von 'String.prototype.length' in dieser Spezifikation.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-standard\">Standard</span></td>\n   <td>&nbsp;</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-properties-of-string-instances-length\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript (ECMA-262)<br><small lang=\"de\">Die Definition von 'String.prototype.length' in dieser Spezifikation.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-living\">Lebender Standard</span></td>\n   <td>&nbsp;</td>\n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table>"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browserkompatibilität","id":"browserkompatibilität","isH3":false,"query":"javascript.builtins.String.length","dataURL":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String/length/bcd.json"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p></p><p></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"Siehe auch","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a class=\"external\" href=\"http://developer.teradata.com/blog/jasonstrimpel/2011/11/javascript-string-length-and-internationalizing-web-applications\" rel=\" noopener\">JavaScript <code>String.length</code> and Internationalizing Web Applications</a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Beschreibung","id":"description"},{"text":"Beispiele","id":"examples"},{"text":"Spezifikationen","id":"spezifikationen"},{"text":"Browserkompatibilität","id":"browserkompatibilität"},{"text":"Siehe auch","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"Die length Eigenschaft repräsentiert die Länge eines Strings.","popularity":0.0013,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"String length","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)"},{"title":"String.length","locale":"es","native":"Español"},{"title":"String.length","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"String length","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"String.length","locale":"ko","native":"한국어"},{"title":"String.length","locale":"pt-BR","native":"Português (do Brasil)"},{"title":"String.length","locale":"ru","nativ